      Beliefs and Ideas
      [edit source]

      This Section Describes the Beliefs and Ideas of
      Anarcho-Buniism
      . These include
      Anarcho-Buniism
      's philosophical, economic, political, anthropological, linguistic, psychological, sociological, historical and geopolitical beliefs along with the methods by which
      Anarcho-Buniism
      seeks to realize these beliefs.

      Philosophy
      [edit source]

      Anarcho-Buniism as an Ideology is influenced by Philosophers such as Immanuel Kant, Jean-Jacques Rousseau, Johann Caspar Schmidt and Albert Camus. [WIP]

      Epistomology
      [edit source]

      Anarcho-Buniism's epistemology is influenced by Immanuel Kant with that Anarcho-Buniism believes in Transcendental idealism epistemologically speaking. It believes in the world of the phenomenal and in the existence of the noumenal world. With that Anarcho-Buniism believes in the idea that a priori concepts form the basis of our perception of reality. Through the a priori, we can only experience the phenomenal world and never the noumenal world. [WIP]

      Meta-Ethics
      [edit source]

      Anarcho-Buniism's meta-ethics are very much influenced by Jean-Jacques Rousseau, Immanuel Kant, and Johann Caspar Schmidt. Stirner's influence is extremely prevalent in AnBuns meta-ethics.
      [WIP]

      Are Ethics Inherent To Animals/Humans?
      [edit source]

      Anarcho-Buniism believes that ethics aren't inherent to any species reasoning being that all forms of ethics are constructed as a means of social control by restricting them and by possessing their mind with the phantasm of morality but there are also upsides to morality[Note 1].
      Along with this Anarcho-Buniism also believes that since Ethics are a construct that they are not inherent to a person but more so that ethical behavior is acquired through repeated actions, traditions, etc. This means that if a person is born in the state of nature and survives in the state of nature on their own they would not learn how to act ethically and what it means to act unethically.
      [WIP]

      Should Ethics Exist
      [edit source]

      Anarcho-Buniism advocates for the fact that people should adopt a system of ethics or develop a personal system of ethics but is also accepting of moral nihilism engaging in a kind of voluntarism with morals whereby one knows the things about morals that contribute to them being a bad influence on one's life but can voluntarily choose to engage in them to use the advantages morality brings. [WIP]

      What Is Required For Ethics To Exist?
      [edit source]

      For ethics to exist there needs to be two ground assumptions.

      1. Free will exists.
      2. For an action to be moral or immoral there always needs to be a subject and an object.

      One may ask why does free will need to exist for ethics to exist? The answer is simple if the subject (the animal doing the action) does not possess free will how can its action even be judged? It had no choice in making that decision so they are in almost all cases not responsible for it so without free will there would be no system of ethics in any existing world.
      Of course, Anarcho-Buniism recognizes the fact that no decision is made purely based on free will in many cases the decision is influenced by external factors the subject does not have control over like systematic pressures for example.
      The second assumption is one influenced by the consequentialist line of thinking and by the thinker Jean-Jacques Rousseau who stated that if a subject is in isolation in the state of nature around no object (animal or person that action happens to) then no action can be moral or immoral due to the fact that the action of the person or animal can not impact another person or animal making the action inconsequential and thus not able to be judged morally.
      [WIP]

      Personality
      [edit source]

      Anarcho-Buniism is generally very hopeful for the future and the eventual struggle that will come. Simultaneously, it provides overly pessimistic predictions for the things that will occur with any event. It frequently tries distracting from this pessimism by listening to old union songs or other leftist songs. Anarcho-Buniism enjoys larping in Kaiserreich but equally enjoys trying to be a brutal tyrant in Minecraft.

      Relationships
      [edit source]

      The relationships between
      Anarcho-Buniism
      and other ideologies is not really determined by specific policies or general feelings, but rather based off a scale (the rating of self inserts is not based of off the user who belives in the ideology more just the ideology itself). The scale ranks ideologies in the following 5 categories:
      • Allies
        : In line with the Anarcho-Buniist philosophy.
      • Friends
        : Indirectly favorable according to Anarcho-Buniism.
      • Frenemies
        : Neutral/indifferent according to Anarcho-Buniism.
      • Enemies
        : Indirectly opposed to Anarcho-Buniism.
      • Archenemies
        : Completly opposed to Anarcho-Buniism.

      • Economic Fascism - I feel nothing except hatred for what you have done to syndicalism and for the fact you have allowed the creation of the modern regressive/reformist 'left'.
